definitions.definition: A narrow street or passageway , especially one through the middle of a block giving access to the rear of lots of buildings.
examples: The parking lot to my friend's apartment building is in the alley .

definitions.definition: ( baseball ) The area between the outfielders .
examples: He hit one deep into the alley .

definitions.definition: ( bowling ) An establishment where bowling is played.
( bowling ) An elongated wooden strip of floor along which a bowling ball is rolled.
( tennis ) The extra area between the sidelines or tramlines on a tennis court that is used for doubles matches.
A walk or passage in a garden or park, bordered by rows of trees or bushes.
A passageway between rows of pews in a church .
( perspective drawing ) Any passage having the entrance represented as wider than the exit, so as to give the appearance of length.
The space between two rows of compositors ' stands in a printing office.
( informal , rare ) A group of clowns ; the collective noun for clowns.
